post_text: Congratulations to Evelyn Page, Windsor School's Student of the Month for May. Evelyn is an intelligent, hard-working, self-directed student who is a positive role model. She is the secretary for the junior class, a leader in the Athletic Leadership Council, a member of the Prom Committee and the Model UN, and an integral part of the girls basketball and soccer teams. According to her teachers, Evelyn is ‚Äúa true leader with a quiet, pleasant, respectful, consistent leadership style who is definitely worthy of recognition‚Äù. In the classroom, Evelyn always seems genuinely interested in learning what is being presented. She has brought this same enthusiasm for learning into her on-line classes as we have moved to virtual learning. Evelyn excels in academics, athletics, and leadership activities while truly maintaining a humble, polite, and kind demeanor. Congratulations Evelyn.

post_text:
Schools Closed - Friday, February 7th:

Dear Staff, Parents and Caregivers:

We have decided to close all schools in the Windsor Southeast Supervisory Union today. This was based as much on the forecast as it was on the current conditions. It looks like the line of snow and freezing rain will come directly through the upper valley. I always want to fault on the side of caution. As I have said before, these are never easy decisions. We have also experienced a lot of student and staff sickness over the last couple of weeks. Perhaps this extended weekend will help us to eradicate whatever bug seems to be lingering.

Have a great weekend and stay safe!

Dr. David Baker
Superintendent of Schools
Windsor Southeast SU.
